	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=232799><span id= >cabilisianecro</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The spell isnt totally useless, but without any type of magic debuff before you attempt to land charm it rarely seems to last close to full duration.<br><br>I rarely use this spell anymore unless I have an enchanter handy to tash it beforehand.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have an enchanter in your group its golden (preferably with howl of tashan)<br><br>I also have a 65 Druid bot that I 2-box with, and there is a spell called &quot;Glamour of Tunare&quot; which is negative (20) to Magic resist. <br><br>Crypt of Decay is a great zone to use this in, I pull a death knight, mez it with death' silence (30 sec) ensnare it on the druid (lasts 14 min) then debuff its MR with the druid and charm <br><br>After landing that, charm seems to last full duration, with minimal early breaks or resists (basically how it acted before the charm nerf)<br><br>Its sorta sad that Necro's are the only pet/charm class that do not have anyway to debuff magic resist.</p>&nbsp;<br>[65 Arch Lich] Lich Cadiz (Iksar)&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=338408" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=338408</a><br>[56 Myrmidon] Grumplescratch (Ogre) &lt;Azure Sky&gt;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127648" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127648</a></td></td></tr>
